# autollm Agent Handoff

Before doing substantive work in `autollm`, read `autollm/docs/AGENT_HANDOFF.md`.

- Use it as the primary durable handoff for sweep/improve workflow, benchmark flow, and `runllm` integration.
- When you learn stable, reusable context about architecture, contracts, or recurring failure modes, add a brief note to `autollm/docs/AGENT_HANDOFF.md`.
- Do not add transient run results or noisy one-off debugging details there.
